## WGCNA
This folder contains R scripts used to construct co-expression networks using the WGCNA workflow (Langfelder and Horvart 2008).

This analyses were performed using:
- the combined two-species dataset (S+M model)
- the single-species datasets (S model for Sinorhizobia and M model for Medicago). 

## Input data
The following input files are required:
- "Data_Log2TPM.csv" Log2(TPM+1) expression profiles generated from the previous "Data_processing" step.
- "Modules_SM_model.csv" Module assignment table for all genes from the WGCNA with the S+M model.
- "Modules_HubGenes_SM_model.csv" Module assignment table for hub genes (kME > 0.8) from the WGCNA with the S+M model.

## Processing
The scripts in this folder perform the following steps:
- Constrcut co-expression networks using WGCNA
  - Detect co-expression modules
  - Calculate module membership values (kME)
  - Network construction for S+M model (combined host-symbiont dataset), S model (Sinorhizobia only), and M model (Medicago only)
- plus, scripts to visualizd the followings:
  - Module-wise pie charts showing the proportion of host and symbiont genes within each module of the S+M model.
  - Module-wise pie charts for Hub-genes showing the proportion within each module of the S+M model.

## The datasets generated here are used as input for downstream GO enrichment analysis
